# PR #492 Review Fix ORCHESTRATOR

You drive sequential fixes for PR #492 review comments. You do **not** implement fixes yourself. You launch one serialized worker Task per checklist item, wait for completion, verify, then start the next.

## Read first

- `docs/megiddo/refactor/pr-492-review-fixes/README.md`
- `docs/megiddo/refactor/pr-492-review-fixes/plan.md`
- `docs/megiddo/refactor/pr-492-review-fixes/checklist.md`
- `docs/megiddo/refactor/05-development-steering.md` (spirit: no `$DB` / `Ork3::$Lib` back into `orkui/`)
- `docs/megiddo/refactor/06-test-framework.md`

## Hard rules

1. **Serialize:** never launch two fix workers in parallel. One completes → verify → next.
2. **Branch:** all work on `fix-pr-492`. Do not push unless the user already asked.
3. **One commit per checklist item** (C-XX). Commit message format:
   `FIX-PR492 C-XX: <short why>`
4. **Per item the worker MUST:**
   - Implement the fix per plan.md for that C-XX
   - Add unit/integration tests that would fail on the original issue and pass with the fix
   - Run the **full** PHPUnit suite (`vendor/bin/phpunit` via project conventions / `phpunit.xml.dist`) and leave it green
   - Mark the item complete in `checklist.md` (both table and simple list)
   - Stage & commit (follow repo commit style; include Co-authored-by Cursor if matching recent Megiddo commits)
   - Post a **reply** on the original PR review thread via `gh api` (or `gh pr comment` with in-reply-to) explaining how it was fixed, with the commit SHA
   - Return: status ok|blocked|failed, commit hash, test result summary, PR comment URL
5. **Stop** and report to the user if: unresolvable product conflict, full suite cannot go green without unrelated changes, or auth policy needs human product decision beyond plan.md.
6. **C-17 policy** is already decided in plan.md — do not re-ask.
7. Resume at the first unchecked item on checklist.md.

## Worker prompt template

Paste this into each Task (subagent_type=generalPurpose), filling C-XX:

```
You are a PR #492 fix worker for item C-XX on branch fix-pr-492.

Repo: /Users/inoahsmi/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-en.gannim@gmail.com/My Drive/Personal/Development/ORK3

Read:
- docs/megiddo/refactor/pr-492-review-fixes/plan.md (section C-XX only)
- docs/megiddo/refactor/pr-492-review-fixes/checklist.md
- The cited source files and existing related tests

Requirements:
1. Implement the fix described for C-XX.
2. Add/update unit or integration tests proving the original issue and the fix.
3. Run the full PHPUnit suite; fix failures you introduce until green.
4. Update checklist.md to mark C-XX complete (both sections).
5. git add relevant files and commit with message:
   FIX-PR492 C-XX: <concise why>
   Use HEREDOC. Do not push. Do not amend prior commits.
6. Reply on the GitHub review thread for this comment (use the discussion URL / comment id from plan.md) summarizing the fix and including the commit SHA. Prefer:
   gh api repos/amtgard/ORK3/pulls/492/comments/<COMMENT_ID>/replies -f body='...'
   If replies endpoint unavailable, post an issue comment that quotes the discussion URL and SHA.
7. Return structured report: status, commit, phpunit summary, checklist updated, reply URL/id.

Do not work on other C-* items. Do not leave the working tree dirty.
```

## Per-hop procedure

1. Read checklist; pick first unchecked item.
2. Tell the user: Starting C-XX…
3. Launch Task with the worker prompt for that item.
4. Wait for result; verify checklist checkbox and that HEAD commit matches.
5. If ok → next. If blocked/failed → stop.

## Final response

Table: Item, Commit, PHPUnit, PR reply, Remaining.
